"title": "9105: last things",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "9105: last things",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The doctrine of the last things (“eschatology”) includes the subjects of death, the second coming of Jesus Christ, the resurrection of the dead, the last judgment, heaven and hell.</p>\n<h2>Death</h2>\n<h3>Physical death is universal</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job30:23\">JOB 30:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam14:14\">2SA 14:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:12\">ROM 5:12</a></p>\n<h3>The timing of natural death is beyond human control</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl8:8\">ECC 8:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps90:10\">PSA 90:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:27\">MAT 6:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas4:14\">JAS 4:14</a></p>\n<h3>Death is not to be feared by the believer</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps23:4\">PSA 23:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps116:15\">PSA 116:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov14:32\">PRO 14:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom14:8\">ROM 14:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil1:21\">PHP 1:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev14:13\">REV 14:13</a></p>\n<h3>For believers, death is likened to falling asleep</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John11:11-John11:13\">JHN 11:11–11:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark5:39\">MRK 5:39</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:36\">ACT 13:36</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:6\">1CO 15:6</a></p>\n<h3>At the second coming, believers still living on earth will not experience death</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess4:15-1Thess4:17\">1TH 4:15–4:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:51-1Cor15:52\">1CO 15:51–15:52</a></p>\n<h3>Death is the penalty for unforgiven sin</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom6:23\">ROM 6:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr10:13\">1CH 10:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov11:19\">PRO 11:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:12\">ROM 5:12</a></p>\n<h2>The second coming of Jesus Christ</h2>\n<h3>The second coming is foretold</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:64\">MAT 26:64</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:62\">MRK 14:62</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke21:27\">LUK 21:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts1:11\">ACT 1:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:28\">HEB 9:28</a></p>\n<h3>The timing of the second coming is known only to God the Father</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:36\">MAT 24:36</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark13:32\">MRK 13:32</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal3:1\">MAL 3:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:44\">MAT 24:44</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:40\">LUK 12:40</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev16:15\">REV 16:15</a></p>\n<h3>God's purpose at the second coming is to gather his people together, to reward the faithful and judge the wicked</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:27\">MAT 16:27</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan7:13-Dan7:14\">DAN 7:13–7:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:31-Matt25:32\">MAT 25:31–25:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:3\">JHN 14:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor4:5\">1CO 4:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess4:16-1Thess4:17\">1TH 4:16–4:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet5:4\">1PE 5:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John3:2\">1JN 3:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jude1:14-Jude1:15\">JUD 1:14–1:15</a></p>\n<h3>The right attitude towards the second coming</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John2:28\">1JN 2:28</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark13:35\">MRK 13:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts3:19-Acts3:20\">ACT 3:19–3:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim6:13-1Tim6:14\">1TI 6:13–6:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet3:11\">2PE 3:11</a></p>\n<h2>The resurrection of the dead</h2>\n<h3>All will be raised</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John5:28-John5:29\">JHN 5:28–5:29</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan12:2\">DAN 12:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts24:15\">ACT 24:15</a></p>\n<h3>Believers in Jesus Christ will be raised to eternal life</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:40\">JHN 6:40</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John11:25\">JHN 11:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor4:14\">2CO 4:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess4:16\">1TH 4:16</a></p>\n<h3>Unbelievers will be condemned</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John5:29\">JHN 5:29</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:46\">MAT 25:46</a></p>\n<h3>Believers will be given resurrection bodies</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:42-1Cor15:44\">1CO 15:42–15:44</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:50-1Cor15:53\">1CO 15:50–15:53</a></p>\n<h2>The last judgment</h2>\n<h3>All face judgment after death</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:27\">HEB 9:27</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom14:12\">ROM 14:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet4:5\">1PE 4:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev20:11-Rev20:12\">REV 20:11–20:12</a></p>\n<h3>Judgment is entrusted to Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John5:22\">JHN 5:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts10:42\">ACT 10:42</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts17:31\">ACT 17:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev1:18\">REV 1:18</a></p>\n<h3>Those who have not responded to Christ will be condemned</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:48\">JHN 12:48</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess1:7-2Thess1:8\">2TH 1:7–1:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet3:7\">2PE 3:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jude1:15\">JUD 1:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev20:15\">REV 20:15</a></p>\n<h3>Believers will not be judged for sin</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John5:24\">JHN 5:24</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:18\">JHN 3:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:1-Rom8:2\">ROM 8:1–8:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:33-Rom8:34\">ROM 8:33–8:34</a></p>\n<h3>Believers will be judged on how they have lived their Christian lives</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor5:10\">2CO 5:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor4:5\">1CO 4:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:28\">HEB 9:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John4:17\">1JN 4:17</a></p>\n<h2>Heaven</h2>\n<h3>God's throne is in heaven where he is continuously worshipped</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev4:9-Rev4:10\">REV 4:9–4:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa6:1-Isa6:3\">ISA 6:1–6:3</a></p>\n<h3>God's will is perfectly served in heaven</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:10\">MAT 6:10</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:2\">LUK 11:2</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs22:19\">1KI 22:19</a></p>\n<h3>At Jesus Christ's second coming, a new heaven and earth will replace the old</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev21:1\">REV 21:1</a></strong></p>\n<h3>The redeemed will enjoy life in the presence of God in the new heaven</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess4:17\">1TH 4:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:8\">MAT 5:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil3:20\">PHP 3:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jude1:24\">JUD 1:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev21:1-Rev21:4\">REV 21:1–21:4</a></p>\n<h3>All life in heaven is sustained by God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev22:1-Rev22:2\">REV 22:1–22:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:58\">JHN 6:58</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:7\">REV 2:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev21:23\">REV 21:23</a></p>\n<h2>Hell</h2>\n<h3>Hell is the destiny of human beings who reject God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:41\">MAT 25:41</a></strong> <em>Hell was originally meant for the punishment of the devil and his angels.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:41-Matt13:42\">MAT 13:41–13:42</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom2:8\">ROM 2:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:26-Heb10:27\">HEB 10:26–10:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jude1:6\">JUD 1:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev17:8\">REV 17:8</a></p>\n<h3>Those in hell are finally separated from God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess1:9\">2TH 1:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:46\">MAT 25:46</a></p>\n<h3>Hell is a place of fire, darkness and weeping</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev20:15\">REV 20:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:12\">MAT 8:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet3:7\">2PE 3:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jude1:7\">JUD 1:7</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ himself frequently warned about the dangers of hell</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:5\">LUK 12:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:29-Matt5:30\">MAT 5:29–5:30</a> <em>Jesus Christ is using Eastern hyperbole, not intended literally, to stress importance</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:40\">MAT 13:40</a></p>",
